  id: Fibularis_longus_muscle.R
  partName: Fibularis longus muscle Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The fibularis longus muscles are located along the lateral aspect of the canine
    crus, originating from the proximal fibula and lateral tibia. Running distally,
    they insert onto the tarsal and metatarsal bones via a long tendon crossing the
    plantar surface.
  - These muscles contribute to hock stabilization, tarsal eversion, and digit support
    during locomotion. They assist in weight distribution and balance during standing
    and movement. Injury or weakness can impair lateral stability and overall hindlimb
    function.
